{
  "texts": [
    "Conversely, it overpredicts women SADNESS (R: 0.98, P: 0.46) but accurately predicts it for men (R: 0.88).",
    "Because emotions like ANGER for men and SADNESS for women are predicted disproportionately, these emotions show low precision but high recall.",
    "To examine in depth these results, we analyze the confusion matrices (Figure 5) for Persona Instruction P1.",
    "Figures 8 and 9 in Appendix D show the results for Persona Instructions P2 and P3.",
    "A consistent pattern can be observed: When attributing emotions to men, the model consistently associates events with ANGER (as shown in the first column of the first confusion matrix figure)."
  ]
}